Reusable SQLAlchemy Pool / FastAPI Dependency
===========================================

This repo now includes a reusable, instance-based DB pool/session module here:

	postgres/db_pool/

Why this design:
- Works with any database supported by SQLAlchemy (Postgres, MySQL, SQLite, etc.)
- No globals: you create a `db = SQLAlchemyDatabase(cfg)` (sync) or
	`db = AsyncSQLAlchemyDatabase(cfg)` (async) and inject it (SOLID-friendly)
- FastAPI integration via:
	- `make_fastapi_lifespan(db)`
	- `make_sync_session_dependency(db)` / `make_async_session_dependency(db)`

Examples:
- postgres/db_pool/examples/fastapi_sync_app.py
- postgres/db_pool/examples/fastapi_async_app.py

Tip:
If you use SQLite, set pool options to None (pooling is usually not needed).
